OL,3,CWhy we should be concerned that Mr
OL,4,CBates vs The Post Office made a #1m
OL,5,Closs
OL,7,FSecondly, and inevitably, a programme
OL,8,Flike this is unlikely to sell well
OL,9,Foutside the UK.
OL,11,FBut if you care about commissioning
OL,12,Fand producing quality television which
OL,13,Fmatters, questions need to be asked.
OL,15,FHistorically ITV was full of cross
OL,16,Fsubsidies.
OL,18,FPopular, cheap output like soaps and
OL,19,Fquiz shows allowed for riskier output
OL,20,Fnot to mention a large amount of
OL,21,Foutput which was simply not commercial
OL,22,Fin nature at all.
